    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="431"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d431">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.304M28/62.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 26, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>General Bixby, Chief of Engineers, will be officially appointed by the War
                    Department to receive the remains of the <hi rend="italic">Maine</hi>. His place
                    will be taken by the senior officer of the board that has had charge in the
                    raising of the <hi rend="italic">Maine</hi>, in case General Bixby can not
                    arrive at Habana in time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
